main event: Radar operators at Patuxent River Naval Air Station observed two unidentified targets on their radar screens on December 19, 1964.
interesting points: The targets were tracked moving at speeds up to 65,000 knots (over 75,000 mph).
The targets made sharp turns and disappeared from the radar, only to reappear later.
The sighting was witnessed by multiple experienced radar operators, but they were initially hesitant to report it.
No corroborating radar data was found at other nearby facilities.
The Air Force ultimately concluded the radar returns were likely caused by some kind of electronic interference or anomaly, rather than actual unidentified flying objects.
witnesses: experienced radar operators at the naval air station
